<subSubSection id="DDAC6573BB59E85C11A741FEFC64FF7C" lastPageId="114" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="950936F8BB59E85C11A741FEFC64FF7C" blockId="113.[151,1436,1981,2006]" lastBlockId="114.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="114" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
Recognized as a subfamily of 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB59E85F10D641FEFDFDF87F" baseAuthorityName="Schuh and Slater" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[486,638,1981,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pentatomidae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="F1274B09BB59E85F139741FDFC77F87F" author="McAtee" box="[679,1012,1981,2006]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" refString="McAtee, W. L. &amp; Malloch, J. R. (1928 a) Sinopsis of pentatomid bugs of the subfamilies Megaridinae and Canopinae. Proceedings of the United States Nacional Museum, 72, 1 - 21. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.72 - 2721.1" type="journal article" year="1928" yearSuffix="a">McAtee and Malloch (1928a)</bibRefCitation>
, this group was raised to family status by 
<bibRefCitation id="F1274B09BB5AE85C118C46D4FE0FFF19" author="McDonald" box="[188,396,151,176]" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" refString="McDonald, F. J. D. (1979) A new species of Megaris and the status of the Megarididae and Canopidae Amyot &amp; Serville (Hemiptera: Pentatomoidea). Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 87, 42 - 54." type="journal article" year="1979">
<collectingCountry id="EDA17668BB5AE85C118C46D4FEB7FF19" box="[188,308,151,176]" name="Heard Island and McDonald Islands" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">McDonald</collectingCountry>
(1979)
</bibRefCitation>
. This family is exclusively Neotropical, and it is monogeneric including 16 species in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="52B64D7BBB5AE85C11EF46FEFE2EFF7D" authority="Stal. Two" authorityName="Stal. Two" box="[223,429,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Megarididae" genus="Megaris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="114" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A7C2EAEABB5AE85C11EF46FEFEBEFF7D" box="[223,317,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Megaris</emphasis>
Stål. Two
</taxonomicName>
species have been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="EDA17668BB5AE85C121B46FFFC19FF7C" box="[811,922,188,213]" name="Argentina" pageId="114" pageNumber="115">Argentina</collectingCountry>
so far.
</paragraph>
